91
00:11:05,510 --> 00:11:07,120
And he didn't answer my calls either.

92
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:08,170
What should we do?

93
00:11:08,170 --> 00:11:08,940
Let's go back.

94
00:11:09,170 --> 00:11:10,030
Wait.

95
00:11:10,470 --> 00:11:12,470
How can we give up like this?

96
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:14,270
What else can we do?

97
00:11:14,530 --> 00:11:15,510
We can't get through to him.

98
00:11:15,510 --> 00:11:16,580
And we don't have access cards either.

99
00:11:17,410 --> 00:11:18,920
We can only go home. Let's go.

100
00:11:20,290 --> 00:11:22,710
There will be a way. Trust me.

101
00:11:22,710 --> 00:11:23,230
Okay.

102
00:11:25,590 --> 00:11:26,940
Guys. Guys.

103
00:11:27,380 --> 00:11:29,020
Please come here.

104
00:11:29,180 --> 00:11:30,490
Hold this for me.

105
00:11:31,830 --> 00:11:35,610
Hello, Brother. Are you Tharn's brother?

106
00:11:36,030 --> 00:11:36,810
Yes.

107
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:41,560
-You moved in next door to them, right?
-Yes. Who are you?

108
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:43,400
I'm Techno,

109
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:45,030
A friend of Type.

110
00:11:46,950 --> 00:11:48,530
This is Champ.

111
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:51,620
-We're all friends.
-Okay.

112
00:11:51,820 --> 00:11:54,290
We came over today to find Type,

113
00:11:54,450 --> 00:11:56,490
but he didn't want to come down to pick us up.

114
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:58,240
So?

115
00:11:58,650 --> 00:12:01,500
Can we go up with you?

116
00:12:03,130 --> 00:12:04,320
How can we trust you?

117
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,350
You can.

118
00:12:07,890 --> 00:12:09,420
I've called Type many times.

119
00:12:09,420 --> 00:12:10,970
Here. Look.

120
00:12:10,970 --> 00:12:12,280
Here. See?

121
00:12:13,250 --> 00:12:14,200
Can you see it?

122
00:12:16,290 --> 00:12:17,520
Calm down, Cirrus.

123
00:12:18,420 --> 00:12:21,340
Stop eating. It hurts.

124
00:12:24,730 --> 00:12:25,660
We're leaving.

125
00:12:28,420 --> 00:12:31,440
Wait. You guys, calm down.

126
00:12:35,290 --> 00:12:36,130
How about this?

127
00:12:37,230 --> 00:12:39,220
Let's go up together.

128
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:42,160
As long as Type picks us up,

129
00:12:42,950 --> 00:12:44,400
we won't bother you anymore.

130
00:12:44,740 --> 00:12:47,130
Okay? Please.

131
00:12:50,190 --> 00:12:52,180
That's OK, right?

132
00:12:52,750 --> 00:12:53,740
Alright, Cirrus.

133
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:56,690
Okay.

134
00:12:59,670 --> 00:13:00,620
Thank you, Brother.

135
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,010
Let's go, Champ.

136
00:13:06,270 --> 00:13:06,730
Let's go.

137
00:13:06,910 --> 00:13:09,660
-I need to deal with those lovers.
-Are you coming or not?

138
00:13:09,660 --> 00:13:10,800
We are coming.

139
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:13,310
-He's so fierce.
-Do you want some?

140
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:15,360
You're still in the mood to eat? Come on.

141
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:22,880
Surprise.

142
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:24,000
Surprise what?

143
00:13:25,290 --> 00:13:26,590
If you ring the doorbell like this,

144
00:13:26,590 --> 00:13:28,090
why don't you take the doorbell back to your house?

145
00:13:28,330 --> 00:13:29,590
Lend it to me for a few days.

146
00:13:32,270 --> 00:13:34,610
Why are you two here with them?

147
00:13:34,690 --> 00:13:37,580
No said he was your friend,

148
00:13:37,940 --> 00:13:40,230
so I brought him here.

149
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:42,620
Am I good? Let me show off.

150
00:13:43,810 --> 00:13:46,740
Don't trust people so easily in the future.

151
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:49,090
Especially people like them...

152
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:50,720
Wait.

153
00:13:51,860 --> 00:13:53,050
What's wrong with people like us?

154
00:13:54,450 --> 00:13:56,590
We look kind.

155
00:13:56,590 --> 00:13:58,180
As long as we smile, someone will come to us.

156
00:13:58,310 --> 00:13:59,450
As for your face...

157
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:03,930
If you frown, people will run away because of fear.

158
00:14:05,610 --> 00:14:07,890
-I dodged.
-Aren't you afraid of getting beaten?

159
00:14:08,450 --> 00:14:10,240
Brother Type, don't worry about me.

160
00:14:10,540 --> 00:14:11,890
I have Cirrus by my side.

161
00:14:12,420 --> 00:14:14,450
Cirrus will take care of me, right?

162
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:16,480
It is my responsibility.

163
00:14:18,710 --> 00:14:19,690
Come in if you want.

164
00:14:19,690 --> 00:14:20,830
Of course.

165
00:14:20,830 --> 00:14:22,160
You came all the way here.

166
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:24,220
Go.

167
00:14:24,910 --> 00:14:25,650
What's wrong?

168
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:27,740
You stepped on my foot.

169
00:14:27,740 --> 00:14:29,600
Sorry, I didn't mean it.

170
00:14:32,620 --> 00:14:35,050
You two can also come in and eat with us.

171
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:44,330
So, can you tell me now?

172
00:14:44,700 --> 00:14:47,610
Why are you having a party at my place?

173
00:14:48,900 --> 00:14:51,640
I just wanted to meet my friends.

174
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:55,150
Because my friends don't meet much anymore.

175
00:14:55,150 --> 00:14:57,860
Because my friends are too clingy to their husbands.

176
00:14:58,310 --> 00:14:59,460
Are you referring to Champ?

177
00:14:59,460 --> 00:15:00,530
I referred to you.

178
00:15:01,230 --> 00:15:03,130
Wait, Speaking of Champ,

179
00:15:03,130 --> 00:15:07,010
